This paper focuses on analyzing conversational dynamics and linguistic cues in group discussions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing data from an online collaborative game, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses the cost and benefits of group discussions, which could relate to cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
